h socio-economic areas.  Parental involvement is high.  Expectations are high.  Teachers get support and reenforcement in what they are striving to accomplish.  All kids benefit. If you take the best kids and the best parents out of the system, you are dumbing down the system and insuring that it will be mediocre at best.  Since your kids will have to live in the same world as these public school alumni, maybe it would be better for them if the people in their world were more accomplished and able to make a larger contribution to society. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="852" language="en" documentId="2738" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="underemployed25" date="Aug 29, 2013 8:22PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="4" thumbsDown="0" origId="2738" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="852"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>